# Liquid Glass UI (iOS 26 / Lensing)

Port UI to Liquid Glass with **physical** lensing (refraction + reflections), not blur-only. Only change visuals; do not change routing, app logic, data, or navigation. Keep layout order: Hero → Skills → Projects → Statement → Footer. If readability is at risk, use TINTED/FROSTED fallback instead of shrinking text or removing content.

---

## 1. Principles (non-negotiable)

**1.1 Lensing ≠ blur**  
Every glass surface MUST include:
- (a) translucent fill  
- (b) backdrop blur  
- (c) subtle saturate/contrast (vibrancy)  
- (d) hairline border  
- (e) inner specular highlight (top-left → transparent)  
- (f) soft shadow (depth)  
- (g) optional subtle noise (reduce banding)

**1.2 No glass-on-glass**  
Never stack a full glass card/sheet on another glass surface. Overlays on glass (e.g. popover on glass nav) are THIN OVERLAYS (less blur, more fill), not another glass surface.

**1.3 One variant per region**  
- **REGULAR**: cards, sections, sheets  
- **CLEAR**: small controls, lightweight overlays  
- **TINTED/FROSTED**: legibility when background is busy or contrast fails  
Do not mix REGULAR and CLEAR in the same cluster (e.g. project card + its badges).

**1.4 Accessibility**  
- Body text contrast ≥ 4.5:1; large text ≥ 3:1.  
- If contrast fails on REGULAR/CLEAR → use TINTED/FROSTED.  
- `prefers-reduced-transparency` → lower blur, higher opacity.  
- `prefers-reduced-motion` → no bounce/overshoot/parallax; minimal fades/transforms.

---

## 2. Design tokens (central CSS vars only)

Use a single tokens file or CSS variables. No hardcoded rgba/blur in components.

| Variant | BG_ALPHA | BLUR_PX | SATURATE | CONTRAST | BORDER_ALPHA | BORDER_PX | INNER_HIGHLIGHT | SHADOW_ALPHA | NOISE_ALPHA |
|---------|----------|---------|----------|----------|--------------|-----------|-----------------|--------------|-------------|
| **REGULAR** | 0.22–0.30 | 18–26 | 1.25–1.55 | 1.05–1.15 | 0.28–0.40 | 1 | 0.10–0.18 | 0.12–0.20 | 0.03–0.06 |
| **CLEAR** | 0.10–0.18 | 14–22 | — | — | 0.22–0.34 | 1 | 0.08–0.14 | — | — |
| **TINTED** | 0.42–0.58 | 10–16 | 1.05–1.20 | — | 0.35–0.55 | 1 | — | — | — |

**Shape:** Card radius 18–24px (e.g. `rounded-2xl`/`rounded-3xl`); sheet 24–32px; control 12–16px. Padding: cards 16–20, sections 20–28, popovers 12–16. Borders always 1px hairline.

---

## 3. Implementation structure (required)

- **Single shared component:** `GlassSurface` (or equivalent) with props: `variant: "regular" | "clear" | "tinted"`, `as`, `className`. This is the ONLY place that defines blur, border, highlight, shadow, noise.
- **Tokens:** Define CSS variables for the ranges above (light + dark). Components consume only tokens—no one-off blur/opacity in JSX.
- **Prohibited:** Scattered `bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border-white/10`; mixing MUI Box + Tailwind glass differently per component; duplicate glass recipes.

---

## 4. Component mapping

| Component | Surface | Notes |
|-----------|---------|--------|
| **Home.jsx** | — | Keep BokehBackground. Scroll-to-top: CLEAR (hairline + highlight + blur); on busy wallpaper → TINTED. |
| **Hero.jsx** | — | No large glass blocks. Nav: CLEAR thin bar or CLEAR buttons (one approach). “Get in Touch”: glass control (CLEAR/REGULAR); pressed state = scale + spring (skip if reduced motion). Scroll hint: CLEAR, subtle. |
| **Projects.jsx** | Cards = REGULAR | Replace ad-hoc “border-white/10 bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl” with `GlassSurface(REGULAR)`. Cards: highlight + hairline + depth shadow + optional noise. Badges = THIN OVERLAYS (less blur, more fill; no glass-on-glass). Parallax only if not reduced motion; ensure text readable or use tint overlay. |
| **ProjectDetail.jsx** | Panels = REGULAR; overlays = CLEAR | Sheet-like. Modals/popups: thin + tinted, no glass-on-glass. Long text on wallpaper → TINTED content blocks. |
| **Skills.jsx** | Chips = CLEAR; sections = REGULAR | Chips = CLEAR; auto-tint on low contrast. Unify radius/spacing tokens. |
| **SectionHeader.jsx** | CLEAR | Thin overlay; typography unchanged. |
| **StatementSection.jsx** | REGULAR or TINTED | By background noise; paragraph contrast must pass. |
| **Footer.jsx** | REGULAR bar | One glass slab; inner buttons/links = CLEAR controls. Keep height tidy. |

---

## 5. Motion

- Use Framer Motion **spring** (no stiff linear).
- Hover: subtle lift (y: -2 to -4), scale 1.01, spring.
- Press: scale 0.98–0.99, spring.
- Menus/popovers: expand with gentle overshoot.
- With `prefers-reduced-motion`: no overshoot/parallax; minimal motion.

---

## 6. Legibility fallback

- Busy background (e.g. bokeh) + body text → start REGULAR; if contrast fails → TINTED.
- No body/paragraph text on CLEAR glass.
- Optional prop to force `variant="tinted"` for text-heavy blocks.

---

## 7. Definition of done

- [ ] All glass UI uses `GlassSurface` + tokens (no scattered blur recipes).
- [ ] No glass-on-glass stacking.
- [ ] One variant per region; consistent locking.
- [ ] Text contrast WCAG-compliant; tinted fallback used where needed.
- [ ] Reduced transparency/motion supported (media query or feature).
- [ ] Cards look “lensed” (highlight + border + depth), not blur-only.
- [ ] Hero stays clean; glass does not overpower background.
